30#include <linux/err.h>
31
32#include <drm/drmP.h>
33#include <drm/drm_crtc_helper.h>

35#include "nouveau_drm.h"
36#include "nouveau_reg.h"

41int
42nv04_display_create(struct drm_device *dev)
43{
44 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
45 struct nvkm_i2c *i2c = nvxx_i2c(&drm->device);
46 struct dcb_table *dcb = &drm->vbios.dcb;
47 struct drm_connector *connector, *ct;
48 struct drm_encoder *encoder;
49 struct drm_crtc *crtc;
50 struct nv04_display *disp;
51 int i, ret;
52
53 disp = kzalloc(sizeof(*disp), GFP_KERNEL);
54 if (!disp)
55 return -ENOMEM;
56
57 ret = nvif_object_map(&drm->device.object);
58 if (ret) {
59 NV_ERROR(drm, "nvif_object_map, %d\n", ret);
60 return ret;
61 }
62
63 nouveau_display(dev)->priv = disp;
64 nouveau_display(dev)->dtor = nv04_display_destroy;
65 nouveau_display(dev)->init = nv04_display_init;
66 nouveau_display(dev)->fini = nv04_display_fini;
67
68 nouveau_hw_save_vga_fonts(dev, 1);
69
70 nv04_crtc_create(dev, 0);
71 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
72 nv04_crtc_create(dev, 1);
73
74 for (i = 0; i < dcb->entries; i++) {
75 struct dcb_output *dcbent = &dcb->entry[i];
76
77 connector = nouveau_connector_create(dev, dcbent->connector);
78 if (IS_ERR(connector))
79 continue;
80
81 switch (dcbent->type) {
82 case DCB_OUTPUT_ANALOG:
83 ret = nv04_dac_create(connector, dcbent);
84 break;
85 case DCB_OUTPUT_LVDS:
86 case DCB_OUTPUT_TMDS:
87 ret = nv04_dfp_create(connector, dcbent);
88 break;
89 case DCB_OUTPUT_TV:
90 if (dcbent->location == DCB_LOC_ON_CHIP)
91 ret = nv17_tv_create(connector, dcbent);
92 else
93 ret = nv04_tv_create(connector, dcbent);
94 break;
95 default:
96 NV_WARN(drm, "DCB type %d not known\n", dcbent->type);
97 continue;
98 }
99
100 if (ret)
101 continue;
102 }
103
104 list_for_each_entry_safe(connector, ct,
105 &dev->mode_config.connector_list, head) {
106 if (!connector->encoder_ids[0]) {
107 NV_WARN(drm, "%s has no encoders, removing\n",
108 connector->name);
109 connector->funcs->destroy(connector);
110 }
111 }
112
113 list_for_each_entry(encoder, &dev->mode_config.encoder_list, head) {
114 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
115 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus =
116 nvkm_i2c_bus_find(i2c, nv_encoder->dcb->i2c_index);
117 nv_encoder->i2c = bus ? &bus->i2c : NULL;
118 }
119
120 /* Save previous state */
121 list_for_each_entry(crtc, &dev->mode_config.crtc_list, head)
122 crtc->funcs->save(crtc);
123
124 list_for_each_entry(encoder, &dev->mode_config.encoder_list, head) {
125 const struct drm_encoder_helper_funcs *func = encoder->helper_private;
126
127 func->save(encoder);
128 }
129
130 nouveau_overlay_init(dev);
131
132 return 0;
133}
134
135void
136nv04_display_destroy(struct drm_device *dev)
137{
138 struct nv04_display *disp = nv04_display(dev);
139 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
140 struct drm_encoder *encoder;
141 struct drm_crtc *crtc;
142
143 /* Turn every CRTC off. */
144 list_for_each_entry(crtc, &dev->mode_config.crtc_list, head) {
145 struct drm_mode_set modeset = {
146 .crtc = crtc,
147 };
148
149 drm_mode_set_config_internal(&modeset);
150 }
151
152 /* Restore state */
153 list_for_each_entry(encoder, &dev->mode_config.encoder_list, head) {
154 const struct drm_encoder_helper_funcs *func = encoder->helper_private;
155
156 func->restore(encoder);
157 }
158
159 list_for_each_entry(crtc, &dev->mode_config.crtc_list, head)
160 crtc->funcs->restore(crtc);
161
162 nouveau_hw_save_vga_fonts(dev, 0);
163
164 nouveau_display(dev)->priv = NULL;
165 kfree(disp);
166
167 nvif_object_unmap(&drm->device.object);
168}
169
170int
171nv04_display_init(struct drm_device *dev)
172{
173 struct drm_encoder *encoder;
174 struct drm_crtc *crtc;
175
176 /* meh.. modeset apparently doesn't setup all the regs and depends
177 * on pre-existing state, for now load the state of the card *before*
178 * nouveau was loaded, and then do a modeset.
179 *
180 * best thing to do probably is to make save/restore routines not
181 * save/restore "pre-load" state, but more general so we can save
182 * on suspend too.
183 */
184 list_for_each_entry(encoder, &dev->mode_config.encoder_list, head) {
185 const struct drm_encoder_helper_funcs *func = encoder->helper_private;
186
187 func->restore(encoder);
188 }
189
190 list_for_each_entry(crtc, &dev->mode_config.crtc_list, head)
191 crtc->funcs->restore(crtc);
192
193 return 0;
194}
195
196void
197nv04_display_fini(struct drm_device *dev)
198{
199 /* disable vblank interrupts */
200 NVWriteCRTC(dev, 0, NV_PCRTC_INTR_EN_0, 0);
201 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
202 NVWriteCRTC(dev, 1, NV_PCRTC_INTR_EN_0, 0);
203}
